Run script/accesssystem_api_server.pl to test the application.

Database updates
----------------

Currently there is no database update magic, easy to add, but.. lazy. To produce new .sql files run:

    perl -Ilib -Mlocal::lib=/usr/src/perl/libs/access_system/perl5/ -MAccessSystem::Schema -le 'AccessSystem::Schema->connect("dbi:SQLite:test.db")->create_ddl_dir'

Then dig out the new/changed bits of table/SQL, and apply them. Make sure to copy over any data if renaming fields!


Schema change: If your person table has a concessionary_rate column, then add a new person.concessionary_rate_override as a varchar.  Set it to "legacy" if concessionary_rate is true, then remove the concessionary_rate column.


